              "      <script>\n",
              "        const buttonEl =\n",
              "          document.querySelector('#df-97412480-bcca-4fee-94e6-81358016a3b1 button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "        buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "          google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-97412480-bcca-4fee-94e6-81358016a3b1');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f6dcfc4N0Dby"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Preprocess data and split into training and test sets"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HmeZmiSz0KJ0"
      },
      "source": [
        "a) Fill missing values: \n",
        "\n",
        "• For numerical columns (except YOJ, DEROG, DELINC, NINQ, CLNO): fill with the mean value of \n",
        "the column \n",
        "\n",
        "• For categorical columns and YOJ, DEROG, DELINC, NINQ, CLNO: fill with the most frequent value "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6vSlDBAlruHl"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Continous variables \n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract all numerical parameters \n",
        "numerics = ['int16', 'int32', 'int64', 'float16', 'float32', 'float64']\n",
        "numerical_parameters = credit_data.select_dtypes(include=numerics)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Remove unwanted columns\n",
        "not_good = ['YOJ', 'DEROG', 'DELINQ', 'NINQ', 'CLNO']\n",
        "numerical_parameters = numerical_parameters.drop(not_good, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Replace nan:s with mean\n",
        "column_means = numerical_parameters.mean()\n",
        "numerical_parameters = numerical_parameters.fillna(column_means)"

      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6vSlDBAlruHl"
      },
      "execution_count": 255,
      "outputs": []

      ]

    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rOBryrtsa-mw"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Categorical variables\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract variables that are not numerical (and the others)\n",
        "all_cols = credit_data.columns\n",
        "num_cols = numerical_parameters.columns\n",
        "cate_cols = list(set(all_cols) - set(num_cols))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get date from these columsn\n",
        "categorical_parameters = credit_data[cate_cols]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fill nans with most common value in that column\n",
        "categorical_parameters = categorical_parameters.apply(lambda x:x.fillna(x.value_counts().index[0]))"

      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "rOBryrtsa-mw"
      },
      "execution_count": 256,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Merge the numerical data with the categorical and other data\n",
        "frames = [numerical_parameters, categorical_parameters]\n",
        "\n",
        "credit_data = pd.concat(frames, axis = 1)\n",
        "credit_data_copy = credit_data"
      ],

      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,

              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",

              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",

        "# Create dummy variables for Reason and Job (one)\n",
        "reason = credit_data['REASON']\n",
        "dummies_reason = pd.get_dummies(reason)\n",
        "credit_data = credit_data.drop(['REASON'], axis = 1)\n",
        "credit_data = credit_data.join(dummies_reason)\n",
        "\n",
        "jobs = credit_data['JOB']\n",
        "dummies_jobs = pd.get_dummies(jobs)\n",
        "credit_data = credit_data.drop(['JOB'], axis = 1)\n",
        "credit_data = credit_data.join(dummies_jobs)"

              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",

      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "d) Create normalized versions of the training and test sets to be used for logistic regression and the \n",
        "neural networks. Do not normalize the dummy columns. Include the first 10 rows of each data set in \n",
        "the report. To normalize you should subtract the mean and divide by the standard deviation \n",
        "(StandardScaler in Sci-kit learn). Note that normalization of the test set is to be done using the means \n",
        "and standard deviations from the training set. "
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "1I1WrZxjj8K1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Scale data based on training set\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
        "\n",
        "columns = X_train.loc[:,'LOAN':'DELINQ'].columns\n",
        "columns_test = X_test.loc[:,'LOAN':'DELINQ'].columns\n",
        "\n",
        "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
        "scaler.fit(X_train.loc[:,'LOAN':'DELINQ'])\n",
        "X_train_norm = scaler.transform(X_train.loc[:,'LOAN':'DELINQ'])\n",
        "X_test_norm = scaler.transform(X_test.loc[:,'LOAN':'DELINQ'])\n",
        "\n",
        "X_train_norm = pd.DataFrame(X_train_norm, columns = columns)\n",
        "X_train_norm = pd.concat([X_train_norm, X_train.loc[:,'DebtCon':]], axis = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "X_test_norm = pd.DataFrame(X_test_norm, columns = columns_test, index = X_test.index)\n",
        "X_test_norm = pd.concat([X_test_norm, X_test.loc[:,'DebtCon':]], axis = 1)"
      ],

              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-d2dc64d4-6ef5-43a7-bc54-dbc0bc70276f');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",

              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",

              "        }\n",

      "source": [
        "d) Create normalized versions of the training and test sets to be used for logistic regression and the \n",
        "neural networks. Do not normalize the dummy columns. Include the first 10 rows of each data set in \n",
        "the report. To normalize you should subtract the mean and divide by the standard deviation \n",
        "(StandardScaler in Sci-kit learn). Note that normalization of the test set is to be done using the means \n",
        "and standard deviations from the training set. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "iQyzH8Chj_g7"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Create scaler\n",
        "scaler = sklearn.preprocessing.StandardScaler()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Extract data to normalize \n",
        "data_scl = credit_data.iloc[:,1:11]\n",
        "columns_scl = credit_data.iloc[:,1:11].columns\n",
        "response = credit_data.iloc[:,0]\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fit scaler to data\n",
        "scaler.fit(data_scl)\n",
        "scaled_data = scaler.transform(data_scl)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create dataframe from scaled data\n",
        "credit_data_scl = pd.DataFrame(scaled_data, columns=columns_scl)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Add dummy variables to data again\n",
        "credit_data_scl = credit_data_scl.join(dummies_reason)\n",
        "credit_data_scl = credit_data_scl.join(dummies_jobs)\n",
        "credit_data_scl.insert(0, column='BAD', value='')\n",
        "credit_data_scl['BAD'] = response"
      ]
    },
    {

      "execution_count": null,

        "#Training data\n",

        "#Test data\n",
        "test_scl = credit_data_scl.iloc[idx:,:]"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# ROC plot and calculate AUC\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score\n",
        "\n",
        "def plot_roc_curve(clf, y_score, y_test, method):\n",
        "    # Compute fpr, tpr, thresholds and roc auc\n",
        "    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_score)\n",
        "    roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_score)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Plot ROC curve\n",
        "    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label='ROC curve (AUC = %0.3f)' % roc_auc)\n",
        "    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')  # random predictions curve\n",
        "    plt.xlim([0.0, 1.0])\n",
        "    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.0])\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate (1 - Specifity)')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate (Sensitivity)')\n",
        "    plt.title('Receiver Operating Characteristic for %10s' % method)\n",
        "    plt.legend(loc=\"lower right\")\n",
        "    plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WfDoyNqp5wNK"
      },
      "execution_count": 270,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "y_score = log_reg_train.predict_proba(X_train_norm)[:,1]\n",
        "plot_roc_curve(log_reg_train, y_score, y_train, 'Logistic Regression')"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6R3ydr59-Byu",

              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",

              "        }\n",

      "source": [
        "# Find conditions under max and min probability for test set\n",
        "prob_default = log_reg_train.predict_proba(X_test_norm)[:,1]\n",
        "max_index = np.where(prob_default == np.max(prob_default))[0]\n",
        "min_index = np.where(prob_default == np.min(prob_default))[0]\n",
        "\n",
        "max_prob_variables = X_test_copy.iloc[max_index, :]\n",
        "min_prob_variables = X_test_copy.iloc[min_index, :]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LEYc40fRH4pT",
        "outputId": "3a21a2fb-cc46-4079-ab75-ad5f111edc9d",

              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",

              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",

              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",

              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",

              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",

              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-e5974d3d-b782-4faa-8c55-99bc941a22a1');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "  "

              "        const buttonEl =\n",
              "          document.querySelector('#df-7f31b878-4d81-4bdc-9f59-7b98c2ea6a6f button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "        buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "          google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-7f31b878-4d81-4bdc-9f59-7b98c2ea6a6f');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "  "
            ],

              "      background-color: #434B5C;\n",
              "      box-shadow: 0px 1px 3px 1px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);\n",
              "      filter: drop-shadow(0px 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3));\n",
              "      fill: #FFFFFF;\n",
              "    }\n",
              "  </style>\n",
              "\n",
              "      <script>\n",
              "        const buttonEl =\n",
              "          document.querySelector('#df-20ec3c4d-1273-4411-aa3b-1f4b6a7fd7a6 button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "        buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "          google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "        async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "          const element = document.querySelector('#df-20ec3c4d-1273-4411-aa3b-1f4b6a7fd7a6');\n",
              "          const dataTable =\n",
              "            await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                     [key], {});\n",
              "          if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "          const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "            '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "            + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "          element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "          dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "          await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "          const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "          docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "          element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "        }\n",
              "      </script>\n",
              "    </div>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "  "
            ],
            "text/plain": [
              "                Predicted class (0)  Predicted class (1)\n",
